definitions.definition: An incompatible substance ; one of a group of things that cannot be placed or used together because of a change of chemical composition or opposing medicinal qualities.
definitions.label_groups: medicine , chemistry , chiefly in the plural

main_definition: ( medicine , chemistry , chiefly in the plural ) An incompatible substance ; one of a group of things that cannot be placed or used together because of a change of chemical composition or opposing medicinal qualities.
secondary_definitions: ( philosophy ) A consequent of a contrary .
